stylometry: Our group project examined if we could afford to pay our 5 full time employees $15 per hour to work in our bakery. We used total weekly sales and weekly costs and used goal seek to determine if the demand needed to satisfy paying the employees $15 per hour was realistic. We decided that the maximum demand we expected to see per week was 480 sales. Through running goal seek we determine that we would need 360 order per week to satisfy our pay rate. Therefore it was reasonable to assume we could afford it. However, this was only to satisfy a breakeven point so we would desire the demand to be greater in order for us to obtain a profit.
